   "source": [
    "Os dados de entrada devem ter o formato de matrizes x[$n_i$,$n_a$]\n",
    "    e y[$n_i$,$n_a$], onde $n_i$ é o número de dados de entrada em cada amostra e $n_a$ é o número de amostras.\n",
    "Assim, como exemplo, uma determinada rede com conexão densa possui $n_i$=2 dados de entrada e $n_a$=4. Considere ainda uma camada oculta com dois neurônios, e um único neurônio na camada de saída, havendo portanto uma saída para cada amostra. Portanto, temos as seguintes matrizes dimensionadas a seguir: $X[2,4],\\, Y[1,4],\\, W_h[2,2],\\, W_o[1,2],\\, b_h[2,1],\\, e\\, b_o[1,1]$.\n",
    "![toy_nn.jpg](attachment:87ce24ff-a2b2-40b0-a039-5abff63742aa.jpg)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Assim, na propagação direta (*feedforward*) podemos escrever que\n",
    "\n",
    "$Z_{h1}=W_{11}^hX_1+W_{12}^hX_2+b_{h1}$\n",
    "\n",
    "$Z_{h2}=W_{21}^hX_1+ W_{22}X_2+b_{h2}$. Na forma matricial,\n",
    "\n",
    "$Z_{[2,4]}^h=W_{[2,2]}^hX_{[2,4]}+b_{[2,1]}^h$. Na saída da camada escondida, podemos escrever que\n",
    "\n",
    "$H_{[2,4]}=f_a(Z^h)$, onde $H=\\begin{bmatrix}\n",
    "h_1 \\\\\n",
    "h_2\n",
    "\\end{bmatrix}=\\begin{bmatrix}\n",
    "f_a(Z_{h1}) \\\\\n",
    "f_a(Z_{h2})\n",
    "\\end{bmatrix}$, e $h_1$ e $h_2$ tem dimensões [1,4]. Finalmente, para a camada de saída\n",
    "\n",
    "$Z_{[1,4]}^o=\\begin{bmatrix} w_{11}^o & w_{12}^o \\end{bmatrix}\\begin{bmatrix}\n",
    "h_1 \\\\\n",
    "h_2\n",
    "\\end{bmatrix}+\\begin{bmatrix}\n",
    "b_o \\end{bmatrix}=W_{[1,2]}^oH_{[2,4]}+b_{[1,1]}^o$ e $ y_p=f_a(Z^o)$ com dimensões [1,4].\n",
    "\n",
    "### Retropropagação (*backpropagation*)\n",
    "\n",
    "na camada de saída partimos do *array* $\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}$,\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}_{[1,4]}=\\begin{bmatrix} \\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_{p1}}} & \\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_{p2}}} & \\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_{p3}}} & \\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_{p4}}}\\end{bmatrix}$,\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{W_{11}^o}}=\\underbrace{\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}\\frac{\\partial{y_p}}{\\partial{Z^o}}}_{\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Z^o}}}\\frac{\\partial{Z^o}}{\\partial{W_{11}^o}}=\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}f_a'(Z^o)\\frac{\\partial{W_{11}^o h_1+W_{12}^o h_2}}{\\partial{W_{11}^o}}=\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}f_a'(Z^o)h_1$\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{W_{12}^o}}=\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}f_a'(Z^o)h_2$\n",
    "\n",
    "e\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\left[\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{W^o}}\\right]_{[1,2]}=\\left[ \\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}f_a'(Z^o)\\right]_{[1,4]}\\left[H\\right]_{[4,2]}^T$\n",
    "\n",
    "Para a camada escondida podemos escrever\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{W_{11}^h}}=\\underbrace{\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}f_a'(Z^o)\\frac{\\partial{Z^o}}{\\partial{h_1}}\\frac{\\partial{h_1}}{\\partial{Z_1^h}}}_{\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Z^h}}}\\frac{\\partial{Z_1^h}}{\\partial{W_{11}^h}}=\\underbrace{\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}f_a'(Z^o)W_{11}^o f_a'(Z_1^h)}_{\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Z^h}}}X_1$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{W_{12}^h}}=\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}f_a'(Z^o)W_{11}^o f_a'(Z_1^h)X_2$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{W_{21}^h}}=\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}f_a'(Z^o)W_{12}^o f_a'(Z_2^h)X_1$\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{W_{22}^h}}=\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Y_p}}f_a'(Z^o)W_{12}^o f_a'(Z_2^h)X_2$\n",
    "\n",
    "$\\left[\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Z^h}}\\right ]_{[2,4]}=\\begin{bmatrix} W_{11}^o \\\\ W_{12}^o\\end{bmatrix}_{[2,1]}\\begin{bmatrix} \\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Z_1^o}} & \\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Z_2^o}}&\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Z_3^o}}&\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Z_4^o}}\\end{bmatrix}_{[1,4]}*\\left[ f_a'(Z^h)\\right]_{[4,2]}^T$\n",
    "\n",
    "e finalmente, \n",
    "\n",
    "$\\left[ \\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{W^h}} \\right]_{[2,2]}=\\left[\\frac{\\partial{L}}{\\partial{Z^h}}\\right ]_{[2,4]}\\begin{bmatrix} X_1^1&X_2^1\\\\ X_1^2&X_2^2\\\\ X_1^3&X_2^3\\\\ X_1^4&X_2^4\\end{bmatrix}_{[4,2]}$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
